last_episode_to_air.name: The Misguided Spirit
last_episode_to_air.overview: n Hampshire, it's a race against time for Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai as they attempt to save a woman who's being hounded by a dark entity in her own home.

name: Help! My House Is Haunted!
overview: A team of paranormal experts travel the UK looking into instances of paranormal activity in the homes of ordinary people.

episodes.name: Chillingham Castle
episodes.overview: Three paranormal investigators travel the UK to help families reclaim their homes from unwelcome spirits. Chillingham Castle has a bloody and barbaric history, and a torturous soul still lingers…

episodes.name: The Leopard Inn
episodes.overview: The team travel to Stoke-on-Trent, Staffordshire where Sharon, landlady of the historic Leopard Inn located in the "mother town of the Potteries" Burslem, has seen shadowy figures and been attacked by unseen forces.

episodes.name: De Grey Street
episodes.overview: Sandy, Barri and Chris explore a suburban house in Hull, where the owner is too scared to stay in his own home due to troubled spirits and terrifying portals.

episodes.name: The Queen’s Oak
episodes.overview: At the Queens Oak pub in picturesque Finchampstead, malevolent spirits are threatening the new owners, leaving them with no option but to ask the intrepid team for help.

episodes.name: The Batehall
episodes.overview: The team of investigators travel to Macclesfield, Cheshire to explore this 15th century coaching inn that is believed to be haunted by a small boy and a mysterious grey lady.

episodes.name: Fleur De Lys
episodes.overview: Sandy, Barri and Chris investigate the oldest pub in the New Forest, the Fleur De Lys in the village of Pilley and discover some shocking premonitions.

episodes.name: Great Fulford
episodes.overview: Sandy, Barri and Chris explore a country estate in Devon with a dark history, from a battlefield in the grounds to the spirit of a tormented child. They also meet Great Fulford's notorious owner Francis Fulford.

episodes.name: Fyvie Castle
episodes.overview: Sandy, Barri and Chris explore a Scottish castle that is reputed to be plagued by an evil curse and by the soul of a restless woman, with stories of skeletal remains and blood-soaked floors there should be plenty to investigate.

episodes.name: The Dolphin
episodes.overview: Sandy, Barri and Chris lock down for the night at The Dolphin, an 18th century pub in Littlehampton with a sinister history. But events take an unexpected turn.

episodes.name: The Skirrid Inn
episodes.overview: Chris Fleming, Barri Ghai and Sandy Lakdar visit one of the oldest pubs in Wales. The first floor of the Inn is reputed to have been used as a court and criminals sentenced to death hung in the stairwell.

episodes.name: Balgonie Castle
episodes.overview: Sandy Lakdar, Barri Ghai and Chris Fleming explore a Scottish castle with a history of murder, torture and war, which is supposedly haunted by a mysterious green lady.

episodes.name: The Cage
episodes.overview: St Osyth, Essex is a picturesque village but one building stands out from the rest; it's haunted! The team encounter real malevolence here.

episodes.name: The Corn Exchange, Hertford
episodes.overview: The new look team investigate the 19th century Corn Exchange in the historic market town of Hertford, which is now an entertainment venue. Is the spirit of a highwayman lingering here?

episodes.name: Stable Cottage, Buntingford
episodes.overview: A murder case provokes an outpouring of grief when the team investigate Stable Cottage in the village of Buntingford in East Hertfordshire. Their research suggests the presence of multiple spirits here.

episodes.name: Little Easton Manor, Essex
episodes.overview: The team are called in to investigate this historic hall near Colchester. The new owners have experienced a range of phenomena since moving in. There seem to be multiple forces present here.

episodes.name: The Smugglers, Pevensey
episodes.overview: The team meet sisters Nuala and Petra who are the new owners of the 16th Century The Smugglers inn in the village of Pevensey, East Sussex. They have been spooked by tales of ghostly goings on from the locals.

episodes.name: Uncle Tom's Cabin, Wincanton
episodes.overview: The team investigate this inn in Wincanton, Somerset, and witness some unusual activity. This pub, the oldest in the town, is supposed to be haunted by the spirit of a little girl.

episodes.name: Chilmark Manor House
episodes.overview: The team investigate this splendid manor house on the Wilton Estate near the village of Chilmark, Wiltshire. One of the team members has an unforgettable experience during the lock-down.

episodes.name: Old School House, Morchard Bishop
episodes.overview: The team encounter something they have not met with before when they are asked to investigate a 16th century cottage in the village of Morchard Bishop in Devon.

episodes.name: Coalpit House, Nuneaton
episodes.overview: In Bedworth, Warwickshire the team investigate a council house built on the site of a former coal mine. The occupants removed occult symbols from the property and have been plagued with strange occurrences ever since.

episodes.name: Tivetshall Murder House
episodes.overview: The owners of a seemingly normal house in Norfolk call in the team to investigate why they don't feel welcome in their own home.

episodes.name: Gedling House of Cricket
episodes.overview: The team are called in by the owners of a property in the Nottinghamshire mining village of Gedling. They think their house is haunted by a former cricket star who committed suicide in the house.

episodes.name: Ghost of Grandad
episodes.overview: The team are called to an unassuming house on the outskirts of the city of Nottingham where the owners believe there are multiple presences, including the owner's late grandfather.

episodes.name: Calverton
episodes.overview: The team are called in to investigate reports of paranormal activity in a pub in Calverton, Nottinghamshire - but soon learn that strange phenomena are happening all over the historic village.

episodes.name: A Sinister Attachment
episodes.overview: Daniel and Claire believe renovations on their home have stirred a residual energy. The team investigate whether Claire has a demonic attachment.

episodes.name: The Grey Lady of Sinai
episodes.overview: When Kate asks for help with her 14th century hunting lodge, the team discover a mind-blowing theory and the sinister story of a murdered woman.

episodes.name: The Ghost of Gertie
episodes.overview: The Bull Hotel dates back to the 14th century and is said to be a hotbed of paranormal activity. The team investigate a child spirit that’s been scaring staff.

episodes.name: Possessive Petts Lane
episodes.overview: Krissie blames a possessive spirit for the break-up of two relationships. Could the spirit be Samuel Pett, who lived in her home in the 18th century?

episodes.name: Murder at the Museum
episodes.overview: The team investigate True’s Yard Fisherfolk Museum. There have been reports of ghostly sightings, strange noises and a violent child spirit.

episodes.name: Theatre of Slums
episodes.overview: The team are called to investigate the Groundlings Theatre in Hampshire. A volunteer believes there are malevolent spirits trapped in the building.

episodes.name: Taking the Biscuit
episodes.overview: Georgina and Barry are being troubled by strange activity in their 19th century mansion. The team investigate reports of a child spirit who throws stones.

episodes.name: Looking for Lisa
episodes.overview: Paul and Daveena have been living in a former doctor’s surgery for over a decade. They ask the team to investigate strange noises and frightening shadow shapes.

episodes.name: Ashes to Ashes
episodes.overview: Kelly lives in an 18th century cottage on the edge of the Forest of Dean. Is an evil paranormal force causing Kelly’s daughter to experience mysterious mood swings?

episodes.name: Playing with the Devil
episodes.overview: The team are called to investigate a 17th century pub. The landlord is petrified to enter the attic and believes a sinister spirit resides there.

episodes.name: Never Dead and Buried
episodes.overview: The team investigate unsettling activity at the Trinity Arts Centre. Box Office Manager Lisa has worked there for 20 years and fears going into certain rooms.

episodes.name: Bargain to Burden
episodes.overview: The team investigate a home in the former mining village of Ynyshir. Can they identify a menacing spirit and finally bring peace to this property?

episodes.name: Devil in Disguise
episodes.overview: In Peterborough, a sinister entity drags Kevin out of bed and leaves him with painful scratches. The team conduct an intense investigation to uncover the demon.

episodes.name: The Curse Of The Jinn
episodes.overview: The team embarks on their most terrifying case yet, as Ian, Jayne and Barri tackle a dark entity that is reluctant to leave a family home in the East Midlands.

episodes.name: Unfinished Business
episodes.overview: The team heads to Somerset to unravel 700 years of history in an attempt to get to the bottom of what's haunting a historic hotel.

episodes.name: Shook To The Core
episodes.overview: The team is called to the south coast by the owner of a haunted home in Kent, who is too terrified to sleep. Ian, Jayne, and Barri come face to face with a demonic entity that takes them by surprise.

episodes.name: Nightmare In Neath
episodes.overview: The team heads to South Wales, where they've been asked to get to the bottom of terrifying paranormal activity on an unprecedented scale at a house located in the middle of an area shrouded in folklore and legend.

episodes.name: Spirits Of The Shipwreck
episodes.overview: The team have been called to a historic seaside town in Kent to get to the bottom of a haunting linked with a shipwreck that may have washed up more than just flotsam.

episodes.name: Law & Disorder
episodes.overview: The team have been called to Bristol to help an anxious homeowner besieged by a spirit whose identity she knows.

episodes.name: Pendeford Portal
episodes.overview: The team once again encounter paranormal activity on an unprecedented scale when they're called to the West Midlands by a desperate retired couple who've lived in a house of horrors for years.

episodes.name: Village Hall Secrets
episodes.overview: The team is called to the Yorkshire Village of Charltons near Guisborough to investigate a village hall that is said to be hiding a dark secret.

episodes.name: The Hanging Oak
episodes.overview: Charlie and her family are being tormented by an oppressive black-hooded figure in their home in Cardiff. The sinister figure first appeared in dreams but Charlie has now seen it in real life and caught her youngest daughter talking to it.

episodes.name: Dead in the Water
episodes.overview: Becky and David bought The Old Watermill in the Norfolk village of Tasburgh three years ago, but it soon became apparent that they were not alone in their new home. Could the sounds of children's voices be linked to drownings in the river?

episodes.name: Highwaymen Of Bassa Villa
episodes.overview: In the historic market town of Bridgnorth, Shropshire the Bassa Villa inn has had a haunted reputation for years. During investigation, the team discover that a brutal murder took place there. Is that linked to the paranormal activity?

episodes.name: The Spooky House
episodes.overview: Rob has recently acquired a 19th century former B&B in the Devonshire seaside town of Westward Ho!. Before his restoration begins so that he can reopen the property as a guest house he needs the team to give it the supernatural all clear.

episodes.name: Farm Of Horrors
episodes.overview: Anita and her family have an idyllic farm located in Bude in Cornwall, but paranormal phenomena have left them terrified. At the end of her tether after her daughter was pinned down in bed by this terrifying entity, Anita has called in team to get to the bottom of the case.

episodes.name: The Chapel Of Unrest
episodes.overview: In their final investigation of the series, the 'Help! My House Is Haunted' team are called to Worcestershire to help the owner of a converted Methodist chapel.

episodes.name: A Sinister Séance
episodes.overview: Terina has experienced terrifying paranormal activity in her childhood home, including an aggressive spirit who loves taunting her.

episodes.name: Forgotten Phantoms
episodes.overview: Desperate Stefan needs help proving his Elizabethan farmhouse is filled with spirits of the past.

episodes.name: The Demon of Donegal
episodes.overview: A brutal double murder, spiritually charged ley lines, and an ancient Druid ritual site spell disaster at a notoriously haunted home in County Donegal, Ireland. But will the team find an unusual ally amidst the chaos?

episodes.name: The Secret Cellar
episodes.overview: During refurbishment of The Swan Hotel, landlords Harry and Jason found a door to a cellar. Opening the cellar unleashed shadow figures and a negative entity who delights in taunting them by playing threatening songs on their sound system.

episodes.name: The Witches of Leigh
episodes.overview: In a horrifying investigation, Ian performs an exorcism to save a family in Essex. Knowing it will take everything to save them, Jayne makes a desperate plea for help from the spirits of witches she believes used to inhabit the area.

episodes.name: Crying Girl of Comber
episodes.overview: The team travel to Comber, County Down, where they visit an 18th-century farmhouse belonging to a veterinary nurse, Allison. She resides there with her husband and two daughters and is experiencing unusual occurrences on the property.

episodes.name: The Man Behind the Curtain
episodes.overview: Since he was a child Noah has experienced creepy visions of a man hiding behind his bedroom curtains. As a child the figure seemed like a protective spirit to Noah but now he has moved in with his girlfriend the spirit has turned sinister.

episodes.name: Heartbreak House
episodes.overview: An oppressive force has tormented Sonia and Baz ever since they extended their house. On the verge of splitting up, they need help. The team must work quickly to bring peace to the property, reclaim the house and save the relationship.

episodes.name: Inherited House of Hell
episodes.overview: Lucy inherited her father's property in Norfolk and hopes to give it to her son Ben. But neither of them can step foot inside after experiencing inexplicable horror. The team battle to rid the house of imps to make it habitable once again.

episodes.name: Shadow Man
episodes.overview: In Worcestershire, Emma is harassed by spirits prompting her husband to call the team for help. One such spirit is Shadow Man and he won't give her up without a fight, so Ian takes extreme measures to save her.

episodes.name: Footprints of the Past
episodes.overview: Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai travel to Maldon in Essex where a mysterious little footprint has appeared in wet paint during redecoration and the team capture a photo of a little girl providing a clue to a historic haunting.

episodes.name: House on the Hill
episodes.overview: An isolated farmhouse in County Durham is the scene of some terrifying paranormal activity including the homeowners being attacked in bed as the team come together to help a family living in fear.

episodes.name: The Winsford Soul Tapper
episodes.overview: Sadie has completely changed since she visited a dark witch. The team discovers a disturbing practice called Soul Tapping could be to blame.

episodes.name: Pit of Despair
episodes.overview: Dave and Linda's home in County Durham is being plagued by a Poltergeist. The team finds a distraught spirit that is causing havoc to get attention.

episodes.name: Hotel of Horrors
episodes.overview: Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai investigate a hotel in a pretty Welsh village which was once the scene of a gruesome murder.

episodes.name: History Repeating
episodes.overview: The team head to Surrey to meet a woman who's return to her childhood home only to discover a haunting that's now terrifying three generations of the same family.

episodes.name: Lost Child Of Anglesey
episodes.overview: On the picturesque island of Anglesey in North Wales, the team take on a notoriously family home that's full of mysterious voices of lost souls who don't want to leave.

episodes.name: Pennies From Heaven
episodes.overview: In Yorkshire, Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai investigate the odd phenomenon of pennies appearing out of nowhere in a couple's home.

episodes.name: The Predatory Poltergeist
episodes.overview: In Portsmouth, a poltergeist pushes the Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai to their limits as they help a family pushed to the brink by demonic dark forces.

episodes.name: The Misguided Spirit
episodes.overview: n Hampshire, it's a race against time for Ian Lawman, Jayne Harris and Barri Ghai as they attempt to save a woman who's being hounded by a dark entity in her own home.
